        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-08 15:53:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> This patch should probably have been merged with https://review.whamcloud.com/55966 to avoid build/test overhead for just fixing a few spelling errors in each patch. \n\nif only we had a way to skip builds for \"no code changes\" patches.\nThe model I found these with takes considerably longer to run so I did not know so many would be found with it after a first pass with much faster models.\n\n> Also, I would still prefer that all of these patches be pushed separately instead of a series, to avoid future overhead if any of them is refreshed and triggers multiple other patches to also be rebased.\n\nit's significantly larger overhead to do it separately unfortunately, so I'll try to be mindful of it if any refreshes are needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
